      "attributes": {
        "title": "Exploring the wonders of data loggers: a Key Stage 2 adventure",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "These small devices hold the key to unlocking a world of scientific exploration and discovery for pupils! Delve into the exciting world of data loggers, exploring how they can be integrated into the Key Stage 2 curriculum to enhance learning and engage young minds.",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "heading",
            "level": 1,
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "What are data loggers?",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Data loggers are compact electronic devices designed to collect and store data over time. ",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "These clever gadgets can measure various environmental factors such as temperature, sound, and light. The beauty of data loggers lies in their ability to continuously record information, providing a wealth of data for analysis and interpretation.",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "heading",
            "level": 1,
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Introducing the Vu+ Data Logger",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The Teach Computing Curriculum ",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "url": "https://teachcomputing.org/curriculum/key-stage-2/data-and-information-data-logging",
                "type": "link",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Year 4 Data logging unit",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "text": " has been updated to be compatible with the Data Harvest Vu+ data loggers, removing the discontinued TTS data loggers. These data loggers are perfect for the Key Stage 2 classroom as they:",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "list",
            "format": "unordered",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "are compatible with laptops, desktops and iPads",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "contain built in sensors to record sound, light and temperature",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "can record data instantly, without being connected to a computer",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "work with free software specific to primary education",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "heading",
            "level": 1,
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Connecting the Curriculum",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The Year 4 Data Logging unit is a great introduction to using such devices in the classroom, but let’s not forget that these activities can align to both the science and maths national curriculum. Why not consider engaging learners with real life applications, with some cross curricular ideas:",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "heading",
            "level": 2,
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Exploring Temperature",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Conduct hands-on experiments where learners use data loggers to measure temperature variations in different locations within the school or during outdoor activities. Discuss the importance of temperature data in understanding climate changes and its impact on living organisms.",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "heading",
            "level": 2,
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Investigating Habitats",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Introduce the concept of ecosystems and habitats by deploying data loggers in various environments like gardens, ponds, or woodlands. Learners can compare the collected data to identify patterns and make connections between environmental factors and the presence of different species.",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "heading",
            "level": 2,
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Experimenting with light",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Explore the influence of light on plant growth by placing data loggers in different areas receiving varying amounts of sunlight.Vu+ Data logger.",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "image",
            "image": {
              "ext": ".png",
              "url": "http://localhost:1337/uploads/image_2_be7543ef91.png",
              "hash": "image_2_be7543ef91",
              "mime": "image/png",
              "name": "image (2).png",
              "size": 39.85,
              "width": 457,
              "height": 457,
              "caption": "Vu+ Data Logger",
              "formats": {
                "thumbnail": {
                  "ext": ".png",
                  "url": "/uploads/thumbnail_image_2_be7543ef91.png",
                  "hash": "thumbnail_image_2_be7543ef91",
                  "mime": "image/png",
