              "createdAt": "2024-02-15T09:33:27.372Z",
              "updatedAt": "2024-02-15T09:33:30.803Z",
              "previewUrl": null,
              "alternativeText": "Vu+ Data Logger",
              "provider_metadata": null
            },
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "heading",
            "level": 1,
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "No kit? No problem!",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Vu+ Data Loggers are now available to loan from ",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "url": "https://teachcomputing.org/hubs",
                "type": "link",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "your local NCCE Hub",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "text": " to support the successful teaching of the updated Year 4 Data Logging unit. The classroom loan set allows learners to work in groups to complete the unit and allows schools to discover how these data loggers can be used in a classroom setting.",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "heading",
            "level": 1,
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Free CPD on how you can integrate Vu+ Data Loggers in your classroom",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "With clear cross-curricular links to science and maths, unlock your school’s STEM connections and bring all subject leaders to join ",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "url": "https://teachcomputing.org/courses/CP257/physical-computing-kits-ks2-data-loggers",
                "type": "link",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "our free KS2 data loggers CPD",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "text": ". During this CPD, you’ll explore how the Vu+ data loggers can be used in the classroom, with hands on experience of collecting data via the devices.",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "heading",
            "level": 1,
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Ignite curiosity with Data Loggers",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Data loggers are powerful tools that can transform the learning experience for Key Stage 2 learners. By immersing them in hands-on activities that involve real-world applications of science and mathematics, you can ignite their curiosity and passion for learning. ",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "As we embrace the era of technological advancement, let’s empower our young minds to become the scientists and explorers of tomorrow with the help of these data logging devices.",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "heading",
            "level": 2,
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "About the author",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Rachel Vidler is a Primary Specialist for Computing at the National Centre for Computing Education.",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          }
